      "reply_to_account_id": null,
      "quoted_tweet_id": null,
      "retweeted_tweet_id": null,
      "text": "In the wake of Typhoon Sinlaku, @DHSgov and @FEMA continue to support locally led disaster response efforts in Guam and the Northern Mariana Islands (CNMI).\n\nTogether with territorial partners and other federal agencies, FEMA’s top priority is helping identify urgent needs and stabilizing critical lifelines like power, water, and communications.\n\nThank you @POTUS Trump for approval of two emergency declarations providing federal resources and technical expertise, including 400 FEMA and federal staff to assist in these efforts.\n\nOur prayers are with those who have been affected by the storm. We will continue to work around the clock to ensure a safe and smooth recovery on the islands.",
      "text_resolved": "In the wake of Typhoon Sinlaku, @DHSgov and @FEMA continue to support locally led disaster response efforts in Guam and the Northern Mariana Islands (CNMI).\n\nTogether with territorial partners and other federal agencies, FEMA’s top priority is helping identify urgent needs and stabilizing critical lifelines like power, water, and communications.\n\nThank you @POTUS Trump for approval of two emergency declarations providing federal resources and technical expertise, including 400 FEMA and federal staff to assist in these efforts.\n\nOur prayers are with those who have been affected by the storm. We will continue to work around the clock to ensure a safe and smooth recovery on the islands.",
